The five similar species in Central America appear to segregate by climate and habitat, with O. trithrix favoring the warmest, driest, and most disturbed habitats;
O. amrishi ,
O. gymnogon , and O. megabalzani favoring the coolest, wettest, least disturbed habitats (and segregating by elevation); and O. balzani falling in between.
